title: Longest Increasing Subsequence
description: The Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS) problem is to find the length of the longest subsequence of a given sequence such that all elements of the subsequence are sorted in increasing order. A subsequence can be derived by deleting zero or more elements without changing the order of the remaining elements.
input_format: A single line containing space-separated integers.
output_format: Output a single integer representing the length of the longest increasing subsequence.
